    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.31"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">31</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI
                        <lb/>
                    COLUMBIA
                        <lb/>
                    
                    INTER-DEPARTMENT CORRESPONDANCE</hi>
                    
                    <dateline>January 29, 1959</dateline>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">TO</hi> <address><addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                                                     <addrLine>Department of English</addrLine>
                                                     <addrLine>209 Jesse Hall</addrLine></address>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">SUBJECT:</hi>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>This is to thank you for a job well done, as Dean English said, "You are truly a pioneer." I am sure you can imagine how much we appreciate the fine job you did on the University of Missouri's first open-circuit telecourse. I am sure we shall never really know how many people you reached so effectively.</p>
                
                <p>I am sure I speak for the production crew in mentioning what a fine person you were to work with. Thanks and best regards.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Bart</signed>
                    <signed>Bart Griffith
                    Producer-Moderator
                    Missouri Forum</signed>
                    
                    <note>BLG:rm</note>
                </closer>
                    
            </div1>
        </body>
        
